The core change is in platform/mcp-server/src/state.ts:362-369. Current code:

```
export const getToolPermission = (state, pluginName, toolName) => {
  if (state.skipPermissions) return 'auto';
  const pluginConfig = state.pluginPermissions[pluginName];
  if (!pluginConfig) return 'off';
  return pluginConfig.tools?.[toolName] ?? pluginConfig.permission ?? 'off';
};
```

New logic: resolve the permission normally (lines 366-368), THEN if skipPermissions is true, convert 'ask' to 'auto'. 'off' and 'auto' pass through unchanged. This is a 3-line change to the function body.

Existing tests in platform/mcp-server/src/state.test.ts lines 80-92 need updating:
- Line 81-85: 'returns auto when skipPermissions is true' — no plugin config means 'off' default, should now return 'off'
- Line 87-92: 'returns auto when skipPermissions is true even with plugin config' — plugin permission is 'off', should now return 'off'

Add new tests covering:
- skipPermissions=true + permission='ask' → 'auto'
- skipPermissions=true + per-tool override='off' with plugin default='ask' → 'off'
- skipPermissions=true + permission='auto' → 'auto' (unchanged)

Also update JSDoc:
- state.ts:285-286 ServerState.skipPermissions: change 'permission prompts are bypassed' to 'approval prompts for ask-mode tools are bypassed (off tools remain disabled)'
- state.ts:362-363 getToolPermission: update resolution order description
